				<td colspan="2"><span>Personally I think you both should reread your posts. Misquotes, misinformation, and miscommunication are all a part of life.  They happen, as us humans have a tendency to be fallible.  Most of the time they serve a valuable purpose as well, that of stimulating debates.  In this way people learn new things, even if it is just a correction of their misinformation.  In fact, most people wouldn't really want you to fully agree with them 100% of the time.  It would make life more boring, striping away variances.
<br />

<br />
Differences in opinion are as common as backsides.  Everyone has one.  It is just as easy to prominently display both.  It isn't as desirable to have to look at both.  Just as stimulating discussions and healthy debates can be enjoyable to read, both filled with vulgar language would not.  The same is true when they are filled with personal attacks.  Both detract from the whole discussion, and drop respect levels of the intended reader.  Respecting others doesn't mean you agree with them.
<br />

<br />
EQDiva has been my primary message board home since I discovered it several years ago.  One of the major reasons for this is directly due to the fact that the forums tended to be civil, without all the drama attached to every heated debate or discussion.  Please don't turn it into another pathetic, personal attack, childish class site.  If I wanted that I could find more than I could possibly read within my allotted time.
<br />

<br />
Polara Magami
<br />
62 Melodic Disciple</span></td>
